                "question": "Do I need a separate compiler program to run combined hybrid code?",
                "answer": "Yes. You need a C++ compiler utility engine (like GCC on Linux/Mac or MinGW/MSVC on Windows machines) to process your source files into a shared binary library block before Python can access it."
